cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with 3D object detection from stereo images using deep neural networks.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of 3D object detection in autonomous driving.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a cost-efficient channel reweighting strategy to enhance representational features and weaken noisy signals.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses deep neural networks for 3D object detection.
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper presents a new method for 3D object detection that outperforms prior state-of-the-art methods on the KITTI dataset.
